Poor pacing throughout. Sidelined Rose in the weakest way. Not enough time for adequate Adam Driver emoting.

While I was conflicted after seeing it for the first time, I enjoyed it a lot more the second time.  While I feel this movie could have been the story of the entire trilogy, the story serves its purpose.  The connection between Kylo and Rey is fascinating and the duels and choreography of some of their moves were also great.  There was never a dull moment and while some things were left unexplained it was a fun ride.  While it is by no means a perfect Star Wars movie, it is a must-watch and might be my favorite of the sequel trilogy.

I thought it was pretty good, fast paced and the story line was a bit far fetched, but overall was enjoyable. The acting was good and even with everything going on around them there was sufficent emotions portrayed by the actors.
